  <p>
  Wood is a living medium, and the furniture maker an artist who works that life into new forms. <br/>
  Furniture making is not a static activity, with dead inputs and stagnant outcomes.
  </p>
  <p>
  In crafting new forms of being from living mediums, I strive to imbue each piece with the honor and respect that the trees deserve as they’re morphed into becoming part of our daily lives in our built spaces.
  </p>
  <p>
  After all, furniture is but one possibility in the lifespan of a tree.
  </p>
